## Java Standards

- Use Java 17+ features: records, sealed classes, pattern matching, text blocks
- Follow SOLID principles; prefer composition and constructor injection over inheritance
- Keep methods under 20 lines; extract private helper methods freely
- Use `Optional<T>` instead of returning or checking `null`
- Write unit tests for all public methods using JUnit 5
- Validate inputs at service boundaries; trust internal code
- Use `var` for local variables where the type is obvious from the right-hand side
- Run `{{LINTER}}` (checkstyle/spotbugs) before committing
